            Probation
        </h3>
            <p>Being on probation means you're still serving your sentence but you're not in prison.</p>
            <p>While on probation, you may have to:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-body">
                <li>do unpaid work</li>
                <li>complete education or training courses</li>
                <li>get treatments for addictions, like drugs or alcohol</li>
                <li>have regular meetings with your probation officer</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Most people released from prison are kept under supervision, known as being 'on licence'.</p>
            <p> The licence sets out the rules you must follow so you do not get <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guide-to-probation/being-taken-back-to-prison">recalled to prison</a>.</p>

